What is HTTPS?
HTTPS (HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure) is the secure version of HTTP.
It encrypts all data exchanged between the browser and the server.
HTTPS prevents attackers from reading or changing the transmitted information.

What is SSL/TLS?
SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) and TLS (Transport Layer Security) are encryption protocols.
TLS is the modern and secure version of SSL.
They create an encrypted connection so data stays private and authentic.

What are Certificates? (SSL Certificates)
